South Africa became the 53rd member of the  Organisation of African Unity Wednesday in the latest sign of its return to  the international fold.
The new South African foreign minister, Alfred Nzo, attended the ceremony  at the organisation's headquarters here in the Ethiopian capital along with  OAU Secretary General Salim Ahmed Salim, Congolese President Pascal Lissouba  and Ethiopian Foreign Minister Seyoum Mesfin.
Nzo said the new post-apartheid South Africa would work to bring about the  true liberation of African people.
The South African flag was hoisted at the end of the ceremony.
